race.comment: Cliff Brown has got CASTLE ON HIGH (2) absolutely airborne with two wins to start the campaign before a second placing n a leader-dominated BM64 at Caulfield. Attention probably turned to this series, which culminates with a rich final at Flemington during Melbourne Cup Week, after that and CASTLE ON HIGH was kept up to the mark with a Caulfield jumpout, which he won nicely. THE MUFFIN MAN (6) resumes for a new stable, which has made a habit of getting good results with new stock. This is short of his best but he's been placed in both first-up runs and did beat home all bar Toorak Hcp hope Athanatos over 1600m in town last prep. AMBASSADORIAL (3) is also in a new camp and should give a sight on speed. LAKE VOSTOK (8) is an opportunist who gets a nice set-up here. MISTER BUSINESSMAN (5) was a nice winner first-up, will be fitter for that and suited up to 1600m, especially from the inside gate.
